"The objectives of the grant are:
1. Enhance services that support the earliest possible interventions for litigants in person, reducing the risk of their legal problems escalating; 
2. Develop services that are designed around the people who need to use them, by increasing our understanding of the stages a litigant in person moves through; 
3. Build an evidence base of what works, by evaluating the effectiveness of the support delivered by the new grant to litigants in person."

The grant seeks to secure the benefits of recent initiatives by funding three posts within the COBSEO core team when existing grants or secondments finish: 
a) Head of Governance Support (MOD currently funds an existing Director of Governance Support post, with funding due to expire in December 2022. This position will be renamed Head of Governance Support and is included in this bid);
b) Cluster Programme Manager;
c) Membership Support Coordinator (currently funded by a grant from the Armed Forces Covenant Fund Trust, with funding due to expire in February 2021).

The purpose of the Funding is three-fold: 

 to support community groups to deliver high quality resettlement support for refugees through Community Sponsorship, leading to positive outcomes for both refugees and local communities; 
 to grow the existing Community Sponsorship scheme, enabling community groups to sponsor more refugees; 
 to develop and implement a sustainable civil society led approach to delivering Community Sponsorship that engages the whole of society.

